{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17534838","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17534838"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T16:50:41+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T16:50:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15188"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15188","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15188"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.01,0.07,0.19,0.71]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7879"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109962"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7879","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7879"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15188"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92320"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"37"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"3508"},{"type":"tags","id":"3511"},{"type":"tags","id":"3976"},{"type":"tags","id":"4534"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4970"},{"type":"tags","id":"4983"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11643"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19214"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44688"},{"type":"contributions","id":"49356"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109962","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/109962"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 54-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a six-month history of erectile dysfunction. He reports difficulty achieving and maintaining erections sufficient for sexual intercourse. He has type 2 diabetes mellitus diagnosed eight years ago and hypertension. He takes irbesartan 300mg daily and metformin XR 1000mg daily. He works as an accountant and exercises twice weekly. On examination, he appears well. His body mass index is 28 kg/m2. His blood pressure is 133/86mmHg. His most recent glycated haemoglobin (HbA1c) was 8.8%. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in long-term management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Refer for psychological counselling","Commence low-dose amlodipine","Arrange testosterone level measurement","Prescribe low-dose sildenafil","Optimise diabetes management"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with erectile dysfunction likely in the context of poorly controlled type 2 diabetes mellitus, as evidenced by his elevated HbA1c. Chronic hyperglycaemia can cause erectile dysfunction through multiple mechanisms including endothelial dysfunction, neuropathy, and vascular disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOptimising diabetes management\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate first step. Improving glycaemic control can lead to improvement in erectile function and addresses the underlying problem. This would involve reviewing diet, exercise, increasing the patient\u0027s metformin dose (assuming acceptable renal function) and considering commencement of an SGLT2 inhibitor.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrescribing low-dose sildenafil\u003C/strong\u003E would treat the symptom but not address the underlying cause. While phosphodiesterase-5 inhibitors may eventually be needed, they should not be the first-line treatment when there is clearly suboptimal diabetes control that needs addressing.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPsychological counselling\u003C/strong\u003E may be helpful as an adjunct therapy, particularly if there are relationship or anxiety issues, but the primary cause appears to be physiological given the suboptimal glycaemic control.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECommencing low-dose amlodipine \u003C/strong\u003Ewould not be appropriate as his blood pressure is well-controlled on irbesartan.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETestosterone level measurement\u003C/strong\u003E may be considered later if erectile dysfunction persists despite optimising diabetes control, but is not the most appropriate first step given the clear presence of poor glycaemic control as a likely cause.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe management of erectile dysfunction should follow a stepwise approach, starting with addressing modifiable risk factors - in this case, poor glycaemic control. Only after optimising these factors should other investigations and interventions be considered.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Poor glycaemic control is a major reversible cause of erectile dysfunction in men with diabetes mellitus.","Optimising diabetes management should be prioritised before considering phosphodiesterase-5 inhibitors for erectile dysfunction.","Erectile dysfunction can be an early indicator of poor metabolic control in diabetes."],"references":["Sooriyamoorthy T, Leslie SW. Erectile Dysfunction. In: StatPearls [online]. 2022. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK562253/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92320"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15188"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92320","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/92320"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-27T18:09:39+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-25T09:18:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7879"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109962"}}},"meta":{"canD